==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Greyhound
<hw>Grey"hound`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>graihund</ets>, <ets>greihound</ets>, <ets>greahund</ets>,
<ets>grihond</ets>, Icel. <ets>greyhundr</ets>; <ets>grey</ets>
greyhound + <ets>hundr</ets> dog; cf. AS. <ets>gr⟦imac⟧ghund</ets>. The
origin of the first syllable is unknown.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
slender, graceful breed of dogs, remarkable for keen sight and
swiftness. It is one of the oldest varieties known, and is figured on
the Egyptian monuments.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>grayhound</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A swift steamer, esp. an ocean steamer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>greyish</ent>⟦br⟧
